Imagine you're on a hill, and you want to find the lowest point.

4
00:00:18,200 --> 00:00:20,884
You can do this by taking steps downhill,

5
00:00:20,984 --> 00:00:23,668
in the direction of the steepest descent.

6
00:00:23,733 --> 00:00:27,343
The gradient of a function tells us the direction of

7
00:00:27,443 --> 00:00:31,553
the steepest ascent. So, we move in the opposite direction.

8
00:00:31,600 --> 00:00:36,876
Step 1. We calculate the gradient and take a step downhill.

9
